com.dropbox.core

Class DbxEntry.WithChildren

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.dropbox.core.util.Dumpable
      • com.dropbox.core.DbxEntry.WithChildren
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Enclosing class:
    DbxEntry

    public static final class DbxEntry.WithChildren
extends Dumpable
implements Serializable
    Holds the metadata for a file or folder; if it's a folder, we also store the folder's hash and the metadata of its immediate children.
    See Also:
    DbxClient.getMetadataWithChildren(java.lang.String, boolean), DbxClient.getMetadataWithChildrenIfChanged(java.lang.String, boolean, java.lang.String), Serialized Form

      • entry

        public final DbxEntry entry

      • hash

        public final String hash
        If entry is a folder, this will contain a hash that identifies the folder's contents. This value can be used with DbxClient.getMetadataWithChildrenIfChanged(java.lang.String, boolean, java.lang.String) to void downloading the folder contents if they havne't changed.

      • children

        public final List<DbxEntry> children
        If entry is a folder, this will contain the metadata of the folder's immediate children. If it's not a folder, this will be null.
